            Overview
          Heading link



 
Copy link






The Department of Psychology at UIC integrates study of the brain, mind, person, group, and community in downtown Chicago – at one of the U.S.’s most diverse campuses! We are a nationally recognized academic department for excellence in research and teaching. We provide our undergraduate students with research opportunities through the Psychology Undergraduate Research Readiness Program (PURR), offer an internal Post-Baccalaureate program for our recent grads seeking further research experience and access to teacher-training, and support our PhD Candidates through contemporary, comprehensive, and challenging exploration.
Learn more about our programs below!
 





            Academics
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Undergraduate Studies
                    

                Our Undergraduate programs prepare students for graduate schools or careers tracks in education, research, public health, and more. Learn more about the degree programs here!
            












                            Graduate Studies
                    

                Our Graduate Training prepares students to earn a PhD in Psychology while becoming scholars and researchers who contribute to the growth of knowledge in Psychology. Learn more here!
            












